 and Jay families together at the apex of Brooklyn Heights society."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Pierrepont Brothers warehouse manager for 25 years","body":"Henry managed his family's import-export firm Pierrepont Brothers & Co. on the Brooklyn waterfront for twenty-five years. After his father's death the warehouse business was leased to Empire Warehouse Company in 1888 and sold to the Brooklyn Wharf and Warehouse Company in 1895. He held trusteeships at half a dozen Brooklyn institutions and served as warden of Grace Church on Brooklyn Heights."}],"slug":"henry-pierrepont-ii-1845"},"X00517":{"id":"X00517","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1846},"death":{"year":1884},"tags":[],"sources":[],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"HD1537","children_ids":["HD1629","HD1630","HD1631","HD1632","HD1633","HD1634"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1869,"date_month":12,"date_day":9,"location_city":"Brooklyn","location_state":"New York"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Ellen Almira Low","first_name":"Ellen","middle_name":"Almira","maiden_name":"Low","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"ellen-low-1846"},"HD1533":{"id":"HD1533","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":7,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"H00976","mother_id":"X00495"},"tags":["city_planner"],"sources":[{"short":"Moffat, R. Burnham. Pierrepont Genealogies from Norman times to 1913 (1913)"},{"short":"Brooklyn Historical Society: Pierrepont Family Papers ARC.263"}],"birth":{"year":1808},"death":{"year":1888},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00496","children_ids":["HD1537","HD1623","HD1624","HD1625","HD1626","HD1627"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1841,"date_month":12,"date_day":1}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"HD0867","display_label":"Henry Evelyn Pierrepont co-founded the American Geographical Society (1851) alongside.","link_text":"Rev. Joshua Leavitt"}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":[],"notable_blurb":"Proceedings of the Massachusetts","primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Evelyn_Pierrepont","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia"},"bio":{"display_name":"Henry Evelyn Pierrepont","first_name":"Henry","last_name":"Pierrepont","middle_name":"Evelyn","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST014"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Designated the land that became Green-Wood","body":"Appointed in 1833 to lay out the streets of Brooklyn, he set aside the glacial moraine above Gowanus Creek for what would become America's most influential rural cemetery. He co-founded Green-Wood and served as its president from 1864."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"His Brooklyn street plan included eleven parks","body":"He drew the grid of the newly incorporated City of Brooklyn while traveling in Europe in 1833. Some historians call him one of the first city planners in the United States."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Monopolized East River ferries until the bridge","body":"In 1844 he merged five operators into the Brooklyn Union Ferry Company. The monopoly held for nearly forty years until the Brooklyn Bridge opened in 1883."},{"number":4,"category":"legacy","header":"Owned a Stuart Washington portrait Lafayette authenticated","body":"His grandfather William Constable commissioned the painting from Gilbert Stuart in 1797 as a duplicate of the Lansdowne. Lafayette saw it in 1824 and said 'That is really my old friend indeed.'"},{"number":5,"category":"legacy","header":"Co-founded the American Geographical Society in 1851","body":"He served on its founding council for ten years and was first president of the Brooklyn Academy of Music. Pierrepont Street in Brooklyn Heights still carries the family name."}],"slug":"henry-pierrepont-1808"},"X00496":{"id":"X00496","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1819},"death":{"year":1902},"gender":"female","parents":{"father_id":"X00907","mother_research_notes":"Mary Rutherfurd Clarkson (daughter of Gen. Matthew Clarkson)"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD1533","date_year":1841,"date_month":12,"date_day":1,"location_city":"New York City","location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1888,"children_ids":["HD1537","HD1623","HD1624","HD1625","HD1626","HD1627"]}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"social_reform","header":"Founded the Grace Church Employment Society in 1865","body":"She founded the Grace Church Employment Society in Brooklyn in 1865, providing work referrals to women in need. Her daughter Anna Jay Pierrepont led the organization for decades after her death in 1902."}],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM026","landmark_blurb":"Her father Peter Augustus Jay built this Greek Revival m